[2] Canada (Manitoba)
Date: Thu 10 Aug 2017
Source: Manitoba Co-Operator [edited]
https://www.manitobacooperator.ca/crops/aphid-borne-virus-found-in-manitoba-oat-fields/


Oat fields in central Manitoba are fighting off barley yellow dwarf virus. ManÂ­itoba Agriculture's Holly Derksen said, "I think this is probably the most severe that I've seen it." It is unclear if there are other, unreported, cases. The virus also may take root in its namesake barley or other cereals like wheat.

"It does seem like this year [2017] there are some bigger patches and when it is a severely infected plant you will not have seed production," she said. "It really depends on the incidence in the field, but if there are big patches that are affected, there could be some significant yield loss."

[Byline: Alexis Stockford]

